<%layout("/listings/layouts/boilerplate")%>

<div class="policy-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="policy-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <p>
        WanderLust is a full-stack demo project built for learning and portfolio purposes.
        This privacy policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and how we keep it safe.
    </p>

    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>When you use WanderLust, we may collect the following:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong> — your username, email address, and password (stored in hashed form).</li>
        <li><strong>Listing data</strong> — titles, descriptions, images, prices, and locations you provide when creating a listing.</li>
        <li><strong>Reviews</strong> — any reviews or ratings you leave on listings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. How We Use Your Data</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>To create and manage your account.</li>
        <li>To display listings and reviews on the platform.</li>
        <li>To authenticate you when you log in.</li>
        <li>To maintain session data so you stay logged in while browsing.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Cookies</h3>
    <p>
        We use a session cookie to keep you logged in. This cookie is <strong>HTTP-only</strong> and expires after 7 days.
        We do not use tracking cookies, analytics cookies, or any third-party cookies.
    </p>

    <h3>4. Data Sharing</h3>
    <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal data with any third parties.
        Your data stays within the application database and is only used for the features described above.
    </p>

    <h3>5. Data Storage</h3>
    <p>
        User data is stored in a MongoDB database. Passwords are hashed using industry-standard methods
        (passport-local-mongoose). Listing images are stored via Cloudinary.
    </p>

    <h3>6. Your Rights</h3>
    <p>
        Since this is a demo project, there is no formal data request process. However, you can:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Delete your listings and reviews at any time.</li>
        <li>Contact the developer to request account deletion.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7. Changes to This Policy</h3>
    <p>
        This policy may be updated as the project evolves. Any changes will be reflected on this page
        with an updated date.
    </p>

    <hr>

    <p style="color: #717171; font-size: 0.9rem;">
        Questions? This is a portfolio project — feel free to reach out to the developer directly.
    </p>
</div>
